On June 5, 2012, the President signed several laws. H.R. 2415 designates a postal facility in Pittston, Pennsylvania, as the Trooper Joshua D. Miller Post Office Building. H.R. 3220 designates a postal facility in Pine City, Minnesota, as the Master Sergeant Daniel L. Fedder Post Office. H.R. 3413 designates a postal facility in Bronx, New York, as the Private Isaac T. Cortes Post Office. H.R. 4119, known as the "Border Tunnel Prevention Act of 2012," makes it a federal crime to construct or finance an unauthorized tunnel or subterranean passage between the United States and another country. H.R. 4849, known as the "Sequoia and King Canyon National Parks Backcountry Access Act," directs the Secretary of the Interior to issue authorizations to commercial pack stock operators within designated wilderness areas of the Sequoia and Kings Canyon National Parks in California.